#Python Input and Output
"""
Input function are used to take the input values from user through keyboard.
Python provides the built-in function called input () This function gets input from the keyboard.
When this function is called, the program stops and waits for the user to type something.
When the user presses enter, the program resumes and input return what the user typed as a string. 
The print() function display the output in python.
"""
name = input ("What is your name?")
print ("Nice to meet you", name)
age = input("What is your age?")
print ("You are", age, "years old")

Input/Output :
What is your name ?
Aashish
Nice to meet you Aashish
What is your age?
20
you are 20 years old
